    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong> and <strong>carrot[s] </strong>(no need to peel!) into rough bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-with-creamy-tomato-sauce-and-pesto-carrot-mash/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potato </strong>and<strong> carrot</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 10-12 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once done, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-with-creamy-tomato-sauce-and-pesto-carrot-mash/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>chicken </strong>and cook for 3 min on each side or until golden</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-with-creamy-tomato-sauce-and-pesto-carrot-mash/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil half a kettle</p><p>Chop your<strong> cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong>, then add<strong> </strong>your <strong>soft cheese </strong>and mix well \u2013 this is your<strong> creamy chicken stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-with-creamy-tomato-sauce-and-pesto-carrot-mash/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Once the chicken is golden, add the <strong>halved cherry tomatoes </strong>and the <strong>sliced garlic </strong>to the pan and cook for 1-2 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Add the <strong>creamy chicken stock </strong>to the pan and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-with-creamy-tomato-sauce-and-pesto-carrot-mash/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, return the<strong> drained potato & carrot</strong> to a low heat with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong>, a splash of <strong>milk</strong>, your <strong>sun-dried tomato pesto </strong>and a very generous pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Mash until smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>pesto carrot</strong> <strong>mash</strong></p><p>Tip: Don't worry if your carrot doesn't get completely smooth, it will add some texture to your mash!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-with-creamy-tomato-sauce-and-pesto-carrot-mash/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked, wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then add it to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until it has wilted slightly \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy tomato sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-with-creamy-tomato-sauce-and-pesto-carrot-mash/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>cooked chicken</strong> with the <strong>pesto carrot</strong> <strong>mash </strong>and drizzle over the <strong>creamy tomato sauce</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
